@page "/"

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Snake Client Project - Home</title>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="header">
            <h1>SNAKE CLIENT PROJECT</h1>
            <p class="authors">by Brady Nelson & Charlie Adair</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Project Overview</h2>
            <p>
                This project implements a networked multiplayer Snake game client using Blazor WebAssembly. 
                The client communicates with a game server to enable real-time multiplayer gameplay with 
                custom graphics.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>About Our Design</h2>

            <h3>User Interface</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Theme:</strong> Retro arcade aesthetic with neon green/purple color scheme.</li>
                <li><strong>Controls:</strong> Use WASD or the arrow keys to move the snake.</li>
                <li><strong>HUD:</strong> Your score is shown above your snake; the scores of the top 8 players, as well as FPS, are shown in the top left of the screen.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Client Logic</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>JSON Deserialization:</strong> The client receives data packets from the server as JSON files, deserializes them into game objects.</li>
                <li><strong>Canvas Drawing:</strong> The BECanvas element in Blazor handles the drawing of the objects according to the assignment specs.</li>
                <li><strong>Networking:</strong> The client uses a wrapper class of TcpClient to communicate with the server.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>